01:38:43.370 --> 01:38:45.610
You opened the chest, didn't you?

01:38:46.410 --> 01:38:47.050
Yeah, but...

01:38:47.050 --> 01:38:47.850
What's your name?

01:38:48.570 --> 01:38:49.530
Your full name?

01:38:50.090 --> 01:38:51.690
Russell Ian Keegan.

01:38:51.690 --> 01:38:52.250
So what?

01:38:54.570 --> 01:38:56.730
This belonged to your ancestor.

01:38:56.730 --> 01:38:57.930
You are the one, lad.

01:38:58.810 --> 01:39:02.090
You have to finish what he began 200 years ago.

01:39:02.090 --> 01:39:02.650
Forget it.

01:39:02.650 --> 01:39:03.930
I'm just a kid.

01:39:03.930 --> 01:39:09.100
Perhaps you're right.

01:39:10.300 --> 01:39:14.380
I suppose it's easier to hide behind the veil of youth

01:39:14.380 --> 01:39:16.620
than to face the responsibility

01:39:16.700 --> 01:39:18.540
for a brother you despise.

01:39:20.060 --> 01:39:21.340
I don't despise Max.

01:39:22.220 --> 01:39:23.100
I want him back.

01:39:23.980 --> 01:39:26.220
Then accept your destiny.

01:39:26.220 --> 01:40:01.370
Cemetery!

01:40:01.370 --> 01:40:04.440
Now what do we do?

01:40:05.400 --> 01:40:07.080
The spyglass brought you here.

01:40:07.880 --> 01:40:10.840
You'll need these to continue.

01:40:11.400 --> 01:40:13.820
What do I do with them?

01:40:15.180 --> 01:40:18.460
You know, when the time comes...

01:40:19.660 --> 01:40:20.860
Why are you doing all this?

01:40:21.820 --> 01:40:25.100
If all goes well, a few pieces of treasure

01:40:25.100 --> 01:40:28.540
will help to fund some of my unique endeavors.

01:40:29.420 --> 01:40:30.700
And if all doesn't go well?

01:40:32.060 --> 01:40:32.540
It must.

01:40:33.660 --> 01:40:35.020
It's your destiny.

01:40:35.020 --> 01:40:46.960
I've done this before.

01:40:48.890 --> 01:40:49.770
It's like my dream.

01:40:51.790 --> 01:40:52.190
That means...

01:40:52.190 --> 01:40:53.150
Grandson.

01:40:53.150 --> 01:40:57.280
Who are you?

01:40:58.160 --> 01:40:59.760
Sure you know who I am.

01:41:01.120 --> 01:41:02.240
Ian Keegan?

01:41:02.240 --> 01:41:12.640
I don't know about any curse.

01:41:12.640 --> 01:41:13.920
All I want is my brother back.

01:41:14.880 --> 01:41:17.040
The dagger has the power.

01:41:17.680 --> 01:41:35.560
Grandson, do not be fooled.

01:41:36.600 --> 01:41:40.200
What he wants is not what he desires.

01:41:40.760 --> 01:41:43.150
What does that mean?

01:41:44.110 --> 01:41:45.710
All our hopes go in you.

01:41:45.710 --> 01:42:31.360
Grandson!

01:42:31.360 --> 01:43:42.110
Legotechnic.

01:43:42.110 --> 01:43:44.110
When you're crazy about building,

01:43:44.110 --> 01:43:46.110
you'll be building like crazy.

01:43:46.750 --> 01:43:48.510
That's Legomania.

01:43:48.510 --> 01:43:54.860
That's a case of Legomania!

01:43:54.860 --> 01:43:58.380
Legomania is building like crazy.

01:43:59.020 --> 01:43:59.980
The Lego collection,

01:43:59.980 --> 01:44:01.100
each set sold separately,

01:44:01.100 --> 01:44:02.140
batteries not included.

01:44:03.100 --> 01:44:04.380
Greetings, everyone!

01:44:05.020 --> 01:44:06.540
We come to challenge you

01:44:06.540 --> 01:44:08.700
with the taste of our chocolatey cereal.

01:44:08.700 --> 01:44:09.740
I bet you go, Kukku,

01:44:09.740 --> 01:44:11.820
for our chocolatey cereal, Kukku Puffs.

01:44:11.820 --> 01:44:15.020
But ours has an extra ring of the chocolatey taste.

01:44:15.020 --> 01:44:17.340
Ours is packed with chocolatey taste.

01:44:17.340 --> 01:44:17.980
Let's eat!

01:44:18.860 --> 01:44:21.340
Kukku Puffs is a tasty part of this complete breakfast.

01:44:21.340 --> 01:44:23.340
From which chocolatey pump will they go Kukku for?

01:44:24.620 --> 01:44:25.500
Both of them!

01:44:25.500 --> 01:44:27.020
So now, for a limited time,

01:44:27.020 --> 01:44:28.860
mixed in marked boxes of Kukku Puffs

01:44:28.860 --> 01:44:30.220
is an invasion of Puffs.

01:44:30.220 --> 01:44:32.380
There's an extra ring of chocolatey taste.

01:44:33.260 --> 01:44:35.820
And now, sports tips from the Biker My Sports Bros.

01:44:35.820 --> 01:44:38.300
Here's Touchdown Moto's long bomb heads up!

01:44:38.300 --> 01:44:39.180
Heads up!

01:44:39.180 --> 01:44:40.460
It's been a three-point play.

01:44:40.460 --> 01:44:42.300
Off-grease fit into Legoman!

01:44:42.300 --> 01:44:42.620
Yes!

01:44:43.340 --> 01:44:44.140
Sports Bros.

01:44:44.140 --> 01:44:45.260
Spurkin' Ride!

01:44:45.260 --> 01:44:46.140
Biker My Sports Bros.

01:44:46.140 --> 01:44:46.860
New Sports Bros.

01:44:46.860 --> 01:44:48.140
and other figures each sold separately.

01:44:49.020 --> 01:44:52.060
And now, make way for throttle's blazin' cycle

01:44:52.060 --> 01:44:54.140
with a blazin' back wheel of power.

01:44:54.140 --> 01:44:55.420
Just pull the ripcord

01:44:55.420 --> 01:44:57.820
and the blazin' cycle goes a distance!

01:44:57.820 --> 01:44:58.860
Blazin' Cycles!

01:44:58.860 --> 01:44:59.980
Rock and ride!

01:44:59.980 --> 01:45:00.940
Biker My Sports Bros.

01:45:00.940 --> 01:45:01.820
Blazin' Cycles!

01:45:01.820 --> 01:45:02.780
Batteries not included!

01:45:03.820 --> 01:45:04.700
Watch out.

01:45:04.700 --> 01:45:05.740
It's coming back.

01:45:05.740 --> 01:45:07.980
We now return to Are You Afraid of the Dark?

01:45:08.620 --> 01:45:26.560
I'm so soon, are ya?

01:45:29.100 --> 01:45:30.780
You just came aboard.

01:45:30.780 --> 01:45:33.480
Who you are?

01:45:34.520 --> 01:45:35.400
Do ya now.

01:45:37.480 --> 01:45:39.240
Then let's see if you can find me.

01:45:53.450 --> 01:45:55.450
Your first choice was a poor one.

01:45:56.490 --> 01:45:58.090
Not a good start.

01:45:58.090 --> 01:46:22.570
Or anything.

01:46:23.130 --> 01:46:48.380
Interesting.

01:46:49.900 --> 01:46:51.900
Let's see without a fire as we can start.

01:46:53.820 --> 01:48:07.210
Really, you, isn't it?

01:48:07.210 --> 01:48:12.640
Yeah!

01:48:12.640 --> 01:48:13.600
Talking about.

01:48:13.600 --> 01:48:16.600
You said you hated me.

01:48:16.600 --> 01:48:17.160
Look, Max.

01:48:17.800 --> 01:48:19.640
I said a lot of stupid things I didn't mean.

01:48:20.920 --> 01:48:21.560
I'm sorry.

01:48:25.200 --> 01:48:26.160
Can I be on your team again?

01:48:30.460 --> 01:48:32.860
Touchin' very touching.

01:48:34.780 --> 01:48:47.400
I am so moved I can almost die.

01:48:47.400 --> 01:48:49.400
Look, I don't want any trouble.

01:48:50.360 --> 01:48:53.160
But you went through all that trouble trackin' me down.

01:48:54.120 --> 01:48:58.120
You went through all the trouble runnin' my gauntlet and dispatchin' Mr. Noyes.

01:48:58.520 --> 01:49:01.800
You went through all the trouble breakin' into my treasure room.

01:49:02.360 --> 01:49:05.000
Yes, I think you're looking for trouble and skip off.

01:49:05.000 --> 01:49:05.960
You found it.

01:49:07.720 --> 01:49:11.880
Look, I didn't want any part of this.

01:49:13.320 --> 01:49:13.960
You're the one who-

01:49:13.960 --> 01:49:17.000
I've stood guard here for two centuries.

01:49:17.800 --> 01:49:18.920
Waitin' for you to come.

01:49:19.640 --> 01:49:21.160
Waitin' for the Grand Battle.

01:49:21.800 --> 01:49:23.160
I don't wanna fight.

01:49:23.240 --> 01:49:25.560
Then you've come to the wrong place.

01:49:28.200 --> 01:49:32.200
Fight will be a fair one.

01:49:34.330 --> 01:49:36.650
I think swords will do just fine.

01:49:37.850 --> 01:49:38.890
I don't have a sword.

01:49:42.000 --> 01:49:42.480
Pity.

01:49:44.160 --> 01:49:45.840
Then you really are in trouble.

01:49:46.400 --> 01:50:06.090
I'm enjoying this.

01:50:07.850 --> 01:50:09.130
You're forgetting that.

01:50:09.130 --> 01:50:42.080
Is this the grand battle I've been waitin' for?

01:50:43.360 --> 01:50:44.640
Get up and fight?

01:50:45.280 --> 01:50:46.320
I can't.

01:50:46.320 --> 01:50:47.200
I don't know what to do.

01:50:49.200 --> 01:50:51.360
Then there's nothing left for me to do.

01:50:53.440 --> 01:50:56.160
But to put you out to my misery.

01:50:56.880 --> 01:51:01.550
Leave him alone.

01:51:01.550 --> 01:51:04.520
Two boys.

01:51:05.800 --> 01:51:07.240
Two boys.

01:51:08.520 --> 01:51:11.160
Two dead little boys.

01:51:11.960 --> 01:51:13.560
Who wants to go first?

01:51:17.230 --> 01:51:18.190
You do.

01:51:18.190 --> 01:51:32.780
Drollhead.

01:51:33.420 --> 01:51:35.100
There's only one thing left to do.

01:51:35.100 --> 01:51:36.140
Who are you?

01:51:36.140 --> 01:51:38.460
You must run him through with a dagger

01:51:39.020 --> 01:51:40.460
and fulfill your destiny.

01:51:41.020 --> 01:51:42.300
Come on, Skipper.

01:51:43.100 --> 01:51:44.860
Use the bloody dagger.

01:51:46.060 --> 01:51:46.940
You cannot hurt me.

01:51:53.370 --> 01:51:54.250
Use it.

01:51:54.250 --> 01:52:04.590
Mr. Scared little boy.

01:52:05.230 --> 01:52:09.150
You fear the dagger.

01:52:09.150 --> 01:52:17.790
Fear should dim the dagger, Skipper.

01:52:17.790 --> 01:52:32.090
But before that, in little trouble.

01:52:32.090 --> 01:52:33.050
What's the trouble, lad?

01:52:34.490 --> 01:52:37.850
What he wants is not what he desires.

01:52:39.530 --> 01:52:41.290
That's what Ian's ghost said.

01:52:41.290 --> 01:52:42.490
He was a fool.

01:52:43.930 --> 01:52:45.450
Finish, finish the deed.

01:52:45.450 --> 01:52:45.770
No.

01:52:46.970 --> 01:52:47.770
This isn't right.

01:52:48.330 --> 01:52:51.320
You're afraid, aren't you?

01:52:51.320 --> 01:52:52.120
Yeah, I am.

01:52:53.320 --> 01:52:54.680
And I think you are too.

01:52:54.680 --> 01:52:57.680
You've been guarding this treasure,

01:52:57.680 --> 01:52:59.040
but there's no one to guard it from.

01:52:59.600 --> 01:53:02.300
That's why you took Max.

01:53:04.400 --> 01:53:05.520
To make sure I would come.

01:53:06.080 --> 01:53:09.180
You wanted one last battle.

01:53:09.820 --> 01:53:11.420
Nonsense talk.

01:53:11.420 --> 01:53:13.260
Use the dagger.

01:53:13.260 --> 01:53:15.180
This treasure's no good to you anymore, is it?

01:53:15.980 --> 01:53:17.420
But you have to guard it forever.

01:53:18.060 --> 01:53:19.420
I believe you're right, lad.

01:53:20.220 --> 01:53:22.540
Use the dagger and Cutter's Retreat Soul

01:53:22.540 --> 01:53:24.380
may be released from this prison.

01:53:24.380 --> 01:53:25.740
No, it's not true.

01:53:27.260 --> 01:53:27.900
What do I do?

01:53:29.180 --> 01:53:32.620
Justice for Cutter's victims is in your hands.

01:53:33.740 --> 01:53:35.340
Use it wisely.

01:53:36.620 --> 01:53:38.220
Use it, Blaster!

01:53:38.220 --> 01:55:38.480
Did I do the right thing?

01:55:40.430 --> 01:55:42.590
The dagger was meant to punish Cutter

01:55:42.590 --> 01:55:44.670
for his evil ways, and that's what was done.

01:55:45.630 --> 01:55:46.910
I did the right thing.

01:55:48.510 --> 01:55:49.710
I will, Grandsons.

01:55:50.270 --> 01:56:12.670
Ever gonna believe this.

01:56:13.390 --> 01:56:15.070
Good show, lads!

01:56:15.710 --> 01:56:16.910
What happened to you?

01:56:16.910 --> 01:56:19.390
I thought it best to leave you to your own devices.

01:56:20.030 --> 01:56:22.830
After all, this is your adventure.

01:56:22.830 --> 01:56:24.510
Sorry you didn't get the treasure you wanted.

01:56:24.510 --> 01:56:27.150
No matter. Treasure doesn't last.

01:56:27.150 --> 01:56:30.510
It's the adventure, the excitement, the game.

01:56:30.510 --> 01:56:32.830
That's what stays with you a lifetime.

01:56:32.830 --> 01:56:33.470
Remember that.

01:56:34.270 --> 01:56:36.910
Though a little treasure never hurt.

01:56:37.870 --> 01:56:44.490
I guess you didn't come away empty-handed.

01:56:45.130 --> 01:56:46.970
No, but I did.

01:56:46.970 --> 01:56:48.490
We had a deal.

01:56:48.490 --> 01:56:49.130
I delivered.

01:56:49.130 --> 01:56:50.810
Now I expect you to.

01:56:50.810 --> 01:56:53.450
Please, I intend to double your fee.

01:56:54.090 --> 01:56:54.490
Double?

01:56:56.700 --> 01:56:58.460
Oh, well, that's different.

01:56:58.460 --> 01:57:01.210
Maybe we could, uh...

01:57:02.490 --> 01:57:03.210
Val and Dad!

01:57:06.540 --> 01:57:07.820
I don't know who you guys are,

01:57:08.780 --> 01:57:10.220
but I don't think I'll ever forget you.

01:57:14.890 --> 01:57:19.130
Listen, what other little adventures

01:57:19.130 --> 01:57:21.130
do you think we might be able to cook up together?

01:57:24.680 --> 01:57:26.120
Whoa, what's this about?

01:57:26.120 --> 01:57:27.320
You're never gonna believe this,

01:57:27.320 --> 01:57:28.520
but you're never gonna believe this.

01:57:28.520 --> 01:57:31.160
We had the most amazing weekend.

01:57:31.160 --> 01:57:32.280
Wait, let me tell you.

01:57:32.280 --> 01:57:34.120
It's the most unbelievable thing you ever heard.

01:57:35.320 --> 01:57:40.810
Are we gonna tell them?

01:57:40.810 --> 01:57:48.620
I don't think so.

01:57:51.470 --> 01:57:54.830
Rush and Max never told anyone their adventure,

01:57:55.550 --> 01:57:58.350
because they were afraid someone might look for Cutter's treasure.

01:57:59.150 --> 01:58:03.390
And if they found it, they'd also find the ghost of the pirate captain

01:58:04.270 --> 01:58:06.990
lying in wait for one last battle.

01:58:09.600 --> 01:58:10.080
The end.

01:58:11.520 --> 01:58:13.120
Awesome story.

01:58:13.120 --> 01:58:13.760
Excellent.

01:58:15.440 --> 01:58:17.200
That was a really awesome story.

01:58:17.200 --> 01:58:19.200
I declare this meeting of the Midnight Society.

01:58:19.200 --> 01:58:20.560
The longest.

01:58:20.560 --> 01:59:12.640
To the 166 hours and counting.

01:59:13.920 --> 01:59:15.280
Oh, raps!

